DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
"PGstandard.pl",
"MathObjects.pl",
"AnswerFormatHelp.pl",
);

TEXT(beginproblem());

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;

Context("Numeric");
Context()->variables->are(n=> 'Real', a=> 'Real', b=> 'Real', p=> 'Real');
$a = Compute("a");
$b = non_zero_random(-15,15,1);
$p = Compute("p");

$ans1 = Compute("|$a|/|$b|");

$func = Compute("(n^($p)*$a^(n) )/($b)^(n)  ");

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT
Consider the series \( \displaystyle \sum_{n=1}^{\infty} c_n\), where \( \displaystyle c_n = $func \). Complete the following:
$PAR
(i) Compute \( \displaystyle \lim_{n\to \infty} |\frac{c_{n+1}}{c_n } |\) in terms of \(p\) and \(a\).
$PAR
\( \displaystyle \lim_{n\to \infty} |\frac{c_{n+1}}{c_n } | = \)\{ans_rule(30)\}
$PAR
(ii) Based on your answer to (i), the series converges absolutely by the ratio test if \(a\) belongs to what range of numbers (your answer should be in terms of \(p\))?
$PAR
The series converges with \(a\) on \{ans_rule(30)\} \{AnswerFormatHelp("intervals")\}
$PAR
(iii) Based on your answer to (i), the series diverges by the ratio test if \(a\) belongs to what range of numbers (your answer should be in terms of \(p\))?
$PAR
The series diverges with \(a\) on \{ans_rule(30)\} \{AnswerFormatHelp("intervals")\}
$PAR
(iv) Based on your answer to (i), the ratio test does not tell if this series converges if \(a\) belongs to what range of numbers (your answer should be in terms of \(p\))?
$PAR
The ratio test does not give us convergence information with \(a\) on \{ans_rule(30)\} \{AnswerFormatHelp("intervals")\}
$PAR


END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

Context("Interval");
Context()->constants->add(b=>Real(.2841), p=>Real(.8713) );
Context()->flags->set(formatStudentAnswer=>'parsed');


$ans2 = Compute("(-|$b|,|$b| ) ");
$ans3 = Compute("(-infinity,-|$b|)U(|$b|,infinity) ");
$ans4 = Compute("{-|$b|}U{|$b|} ");

ANS($ans1->cmp);
ANS($ans2->cmp);
ANS($ans3->cmp);
ANS($ans4->cmp);




